                                "start": 26,
                                "stop": 34.473,
                                "byte_start": 132639,
                                "byte_stop": 166599,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 02-1196 Securities and Exchange Commission versus Edwards will be announced by Justice O\u2019Connor."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 34.473,
                        "stop": 226.612,
                        "byte_start": 166599,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15092,
                            "name": "Sandra Day O\u0027Connor",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/sandra_day_oconnor",
                            "last_name": "O\u0027Connor",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2736,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 370242000,
                                    "date_end": 1138687200,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2736"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32763,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49563,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/sandra_day_oconnor.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8894,
                            "identifier": "sandra_day_oconnor"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 34.473,
                                "stop": 38.3,
                                "byte_start": 166599,
                                "byte_stop": 181959,
                                "text": "This case is here on writ of certiorari to the Eleventh Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 38.3,
                                "stop": 48.081,
                                "byte_start": 181959,
                                "byte_stop": 221038,
                                "text": "The respondent, Charles Edwards, was the chief executive officer and sole shareholder of a company called ETS Payphones."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 48.081,
                                "stop": 59.567,
                                "byte_start": 221038,
                                "byte_stop": 267013,
                                "text": "ETS sold payphones to the public packaged with an agreement under which the purchaser would lease the payphone back to the ETS for a fixed monthly payment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 59.567,
                                "stop": 67.13,
                                "byte_start": 267013,
                                "byte_stop": 297211,
                                "text": "These payments amounted to approximately a 14% annual return on the purchaser\u2019s investment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 67.13,
                                "stop": 73.745,
                                "byte_start": 297211,
                                "byte_stop": 323751,
                                "text": "ETS was unable to meet its obligations under the leaseback agreements and filed for bankruptcy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 73.745,
                                "stop": 89.768,
                                "byte_start": 323751,
                                "byte_stop": 387803,
                                "text": "The Securities and Exchange Commission then initiated this civil enforcement action claiming that the sale and leaseback arrangements were subject to the registration requirements and anti-fraud provisions of the federal securities law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 89.768,
                                "stop": 106.228,
                                "byte_start": 387803,
                                "byte_stop": 453632,
                                "text": "The District Court concluded that the arrangements were investment contracts, one of the investment instruments included in the definition of security in the Securities Act in 1933 and the Securities Exchange Act of 1934."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 106.228,
                                "stop": 108.462,
                                "byte_start": 453632,
                                "byte_stop": 462618,
                                "text": "The Eleventh Circuit disagreed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 108.462,
                                "stop": 124.357,
                                "byte_start": 462618,
                                "byte_stop": 526148,
                                "text": "It read our prior cases to require that an investment contract offer either capital appreciation or participation in earnings and thus, to exclude schemes such as this one that offered a fixed rate of return."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 124.357,
                                "stop": 138.734,
                                "byte_start": 526148,
                                "byte_stop": 583617,
                                "text": "In our opinion filed today, we conclude that an investment scheme promising a fixed rate of return can be an investment contract and thus a security subject to the federal securities law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 138.734,
                                "stop": 158.266,
                                "byte_start": 583617,
                                "byte_stop": 661776,
                                "text": "In our 1946 decision in SEC versus Howey, we established that the test for determining whether a scheme is an investment contract is whether the scheme involves an investment of money in a common enterprise with profits to come solely from the efforts of others."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 158.266,
                                "stop": 166.072,
                                "byte_start": 661776,
                                "byte_stop": 693018,
                                "text": "When we spoke of profits, we were referring simply to the income or return that investors seek on their investment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 166.072,
                                "stop": 175.626,
                                "byte_start": 693018,
                                "byte_stop": 731261,
                                "text": "Thus, there is no reason to distinguish between promises of fixed returns and promises of variable returns for purposes of this test."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 175.626,
                                "stop": 191.048,
                                "byte_start": 731261,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Moreover, excluding fix return schemes from the securities laws would open up and easily exploit a loophole and would leave unregulated a set of schemes particularly attractive to those most vulnerable to investment fraud."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 191.048,
                                "stop": 204.853,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In light of these factors, it is not surprising that the SEC has consistently rejected the limited reading of investment contract that respondent advances, and we do the same."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 204.853,
                                "stop": 226.612,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The decision of the Court is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
